00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Most people use Claude by typing in a chat window.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,000
I built a runtime around it.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:20,000
367 lines of legacy Flask code.

4
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:36,000
SQL injection. MD5 passwords.
Admin routes with zero auth.

5
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:00,000
This is what I'm refactoring —
without breaking anything.

6
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Here's what that looks like.

7
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Before touching a single line —

8
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:38,000
A pre-flight check.
33 automated verifications.

9
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:43,000
9 slash commands verified.
State DB ready. 0 failures.

10
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Claude reads the entire legacy codebase.

11
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Every smell gets catalogued
into a SQLite state database.

12
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Not in a chat.
In a structured state machine
with 7 tables and typed fields.

13
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Each phase has an exit gate.

14
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Claude cannot move forward
until every criterion is met.

15
00:03:45,000 --> 00:04:00,000
No hallucinated progress.
No skipped steps.

16
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Gate validated. Phase locked.

17
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Every session updates a dashboard.

18
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:08,000
State is committed to git.

19
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Human-readable SQL dump.
Every decision. Every smell. Every metric.
No black box.

20
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:35,000
7 phases · 9 slash commands
SQLite state · Gate validation · Context budget
Built with Claude Code.

